Nazario wins! Even Luiza and Domingo doubted it, as stamina isn't Nazario's strong suit (neither is strengh).

That's glorious, but there's still one fight left, and as we know, Domingo doesn't like exercise. Actually he'd rather chill out.

Has he learnt something from his special training with Bernardo? Fight!
name: Nemcalanos

description: Nancy's in a tight spot. Is she really as good as she says she is? And where did Steven come from, anyway?

Finally, some answers! Escaping the beach zombies, Astrid, Gabi, Dean, Jorge and Bernard drive out to see The Professor at Gabi's insistence. She says he's the only man who can help them. In an extended flashback that EXPLAINS IT ALL, Gabi fills everyone in on The Professor, what he has to do with the dead coming back to life, and how it all ties in to her fear of The Shore.

Surrounded by boys, Kei was certainly having the time of her life in Houou High. But soon after she enrolls, troubles are thrown at her from every direction! Will her roommate, Yui, help her get along or will he be the evil villan that he already is? Or will her classmate, Kousuke, be the true saviour?

Contents

  • Wandering in Dissipation
  • Intentional Junction
  • Symmetrical Detectives
  • Asymmetrical Shifters
  • Return of Rebellion
  • Wolf Barrier
name: Vol. 2

volume.name: The Beautiful Skies of Houou High

description:
Kei's finally used to being around guys, and she no longer loses her lunch when interacting with them. This has led to her and Kousuke becoming closer friends. However, now Yui's mood seems to have soured. Kei speaks her mind on a topic she believes to be the root of Yui's bitterness, but instead of smoothing things out she ends up making things worse. In the midst of their arguments, Yui reveals that he and Kei knew each other in the past. Confusion overwhelms Kei because she thought she'd only met Yui when she'd enrolled at Houou High.

Did Kei forget something important or is Yui spouting more lies? How can she even think about the past when the present is in peril? She's too busy battling Yui's mind-games and keeping her secret from being exposed! Can't a girl catch a break?!

Chapter Titles

  • Chapter 13: Stony Raindrops
  • Chapter 14: One-Way Confusion
  • Chapter 15: Inner Sensuous
  • Chapter 16: Initial Suggestion
  • Chapter 17: Joint Monologue
  • Extra: Ocean:Bruise
name: Vol. 3

volume.name: The Beautiful Skies of Houou High

description: The raptors are still out there somewhere, Blastosaurus just knows it. The only clue he has is a mysterious soup truck seen in the vicinity when they disappeared, that, and a sniveling, cowardly scientist named Jasper Meadon who just happens to be head chef at the Grauman's Soup Factory. Why would a soup chef need a degree in quantum physics?

Olive's wildest dreams come true when she comes face to face with the Sharksquatch; a creature who's part shark, part squatch and all awesome! It's up to Olive to accompany this mythic beast on a magical journey and do battle with the dreaded Leprecabra. The fur is gonna fly in another action packed issue of CAAATS!

Reeling from the discovery that she's wanted for blowing up her father's bridge, Sela and Robb head to Sela's best friend Maya's house to regroup. They aren't the only ones looking for answers - while resupplying in Carapacha, the pirates learn there's a bounty on their heads for the same crime, and Jenny Avery means to get to the bottom of it. The Windbournes believe that their daughter is being framed, but by who?
A mysterious killer who seems to follow in Harper's wake. Will Harper and Tolliver get out of Sarne, Arkansas in one piece, or will they be the killer's next victims?
name: Chapter Six

description:
Doghouse Eight

ONE COMIC BOOK, THREE STORIES. WELCOME TO THE DOGHOUSE ISSUE EIGHT.

"I'M A SOLDIER. I BELONG AT THE FRONT. I'M NO SPY."

October 14th 1940. With the world watching the fight against Hitler in Europe, a clandestine team fights a secret war at home - in CHURCHILL'S BOYS.

"CAN WE TALK ABOUT YOU NOT BEING HUMAN FIRST?"

Besieged by spam monsters, the gang are thrown in at the deep end as they learn of Grandpa's heroic past - in FLIPSIDE.

"IT'S A QUICK IN AND OUT. WHAT COULD POSSIBLY GO WRONG?"

What's the worst that can happen... ? Jack and his team are about to find out - in REPO DELUXE.
name: Churchill's Boys; Flipside; Repo Deluxe

description: Serialized from the pages of Dungeon Quest Book Three by Joe Daly, we join Millenium Boy, Millenium Boy, Steve, Nerd Girl and Lash Penis mid-adventure. In a nearly silent issue, the gang travels from strange place to exotic local as each flip of the page showcases Daly's linework; a happy marriage of the spot black terror of Charles Burns with the detail of Tim Lane.
Our regular Falling Rock crew investigates the existence of the ellusive Desert Yeti.

The penultimate chapter in Penny and Ace's honeymoon saga! Having narrowly escaped severe injury or worse, Penny starts investigating the mysterious super-plane piloted by Dark Bird's sister, Trixie. Even with help from all three Diggers Sisters and (reluctantly) Trixie herself, she may not learn enough before Dark Bird strikes again in their darkest hour!

Every year, the Gold Digger universe grows and provides more for readers to appreciate. Fred Perry gives month after month, and this is his readers' chance to give back. Pro and amateur fans alike present their own takes on their favorite GD characters. Whether you're adding a story or just grabbing up a copy, you too can be a part of the GD universe!

New story arc! PERFECT JUMPING ON POINT! The boundless evil of vampires comes to a small town and lays waste to it in a surprising way. Does Solomon and company truly know what to expect? Take a new look at a classic monster in "The Terrible Fruit Bats" part one. Also in this issue, Nicola (Earth 2) Scott brings you a classic tale of criminal vampires and a heist gone wrong. Plus, all-new back-up stories by Russell Hillman (Dark of the Forest) and Brian J. Crowley (Hack/Slash, GI:Joe).
name: The Terrible Fruit Bats Part One

description:
A botched break-in attempt of the Athenaeum Library ends at the barrel of a gun as Cthulhu Cultists interrogate Lovecraft and Tesla while looking for their own copy of the Necronomicon. In Rome, two old men approach a young artist to discuss the nature of sacrifice.

Note: The digital edition (12/3/2014) for this issue was released before the print edition.
name: History in the Making Part 3 of 3

description: Galahad finds the man behind the theft of his reputation and fortune--but it turns out he's responsible for something else. Something much, much worse.

Published in the 1970s, set in the 1940s, INVADERS was Marvel's best and brightest retro revival of the Golden Age heroes of World War II - and now, the series is collected across two massive volumes! Captain America, the Human Torch and the Sub-Mariner - plus scrappy sidekicks Bucky and Toro - first banded together when the United States entered WWII! Now, relive the heroes' untold tales as they face the evil Axis powers - and battle Scarlet Scarab, Master Man, Iron Cross, Super-Axis and more! But how will the Invaders react when Cap and Bucky die?! Plus: the formation of the Kid Commandoes and the villainous history of the X-Men's Dr. Nemesis! Guest-starring Nick Fury, dozens of GA heroes - and believe it or not, the mighty Thor! Collecting INVADERS (1975) #23-41, INVADERS (1993) #1-4, GIANT-SIZE INVADERS #2 and WHAT IF? (1977) #4.
name: Vol. 2

volume.name: The Invaders Classic: The Complete Collection

description: Nevermore, nevermore, the ravens seem to croon outside of Arkham Asylum, as a mysterious man calling himself Edgar is placed there to be questioned by a psychologist on the whereabouts of Batmans body.
name: Nevermore..., Part 1 of 3

description: In the wake of an epic battle with demonic forces, The Angels of Heaven begin a dark slide into vice.

Enter Extremely Conservative Woman

Who runs the mysterious criminal underground in Rose City? Naked Man finds out in the No Hope for Hollywood. Extremely Conservative Woman takes center stage as a creepy new villain follows her everywhere. ECW teaches a Krav Maga move in Everyone was Krav Maga'ing. Pie-Man guest stars in The Adventures of Pie-Man.
name: Enter Extremely Conservative Woman

description: In this issue: Jason and Frankie argue, Rachel and Harvey perform a ritual and Tracy has a weird dream! Plus, another famous floundering film!

The sequel to the popular graphic novel featured in Rolling Stone! Rock music has taken over the airwaves for decades. David Bowie, Alice Cooper, Freddie Mercury and Bon Jovi are just some of the iconic figures that have formed the rock music genre. This jam session of biographies showcases these trailblazers in this unique illustrated graphic novel.
name: Volume Two
